An officer allegedly manhandled the woman in front of her nine-year-old son. CAPE TOWN - A 23-year-old woman will be in appearing in the Mitchells Plain Magistrates Court on charges of crimen injuria and resisting arrest. A video of the incident was posted on social media platform Facebook, where complaints were made against an officer who allegedly manhandled the woman in front of her nine-year-old son.According to the post, the woman was at the Lentegeur police station to report a robbery incident on Saturday evening.Western Cape Police have confirmed the incident is being investigated.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)